No way to delete files permanently technically
Shred tools also cant gaurantee 100% removal
Inode Table is like Indexes in books
File System/Format (FAT, NTFS etc.)
When we delete a file, entry from inode table gets removed and data remains
reformat means new inode index page
user cant access partition directly but we have access to folder and by m